// Cloud object storage (S3/R2/GCS) is intentionally NOT a native module --
// there's no C code to maintain here. boto3 (or any other cloud SDK) is
// already reachable through the python.run bridge (see docs/STDLIB.md),
// so a thin Varian wrapper is all a real integration needs:
//
//   fn s3_put(bucket, key, body) {
//       let s3 = python.run("boto3", "client", ["s3"])
//       return python.run("boto3", "put_object", [s3, bucket, key, body])
//   }
//
// This file is documentation-only (no live AWS credentials in this sandbox);
// it intentionally does not execute python.run with real boto3 calls.
print("see vn_modules/storage.vn for the local-filesystem backend;")
print("for S3/R2/GCS, wrap python.run(\"boto3\", ...) the same way instead of writing new C.")
